title: Russia’s Retreat in Ukraine Pokes Holes in Putin’s Projection of Force
description: Russia’s military setbacks may be weakening President Vladimir V. Putin’s reputation at home as a savvy geopolitical strategist.

title: Ukraine Routs Russian Forces in Northeast, Forcing a Retreat
description: Russia acknowledged that it had lost nearly all of the northern region of Kharkiv after a blitzkrieg thrust by Ukrainian fighters.

title: Your Monday Briefing: Ukraine Gains Ground
description: Plus China locks down Xinjiang and floods devastate Pakistan’s agriculture.

title: What Will Happen to Queen Elizabeth’s Corgis
description: Prince Andrew, who had given his mother the two corgis she owned at her death, and his ex-wife, Sarah, Duchess of York, will care for the beloved pets.

title: After Sept. 11, the Queen Requested ‘The Star-Spangled Banner’ at Guard Changing
description: It was a break with tradition and a show of support to a grieving nation.

title: Queen’s Ties to Scotland Add New Wrinkle to Push for Independence
description: Political analysts said that respect for the queen and her devotion to Scotland could strengthen a union that has been under acute strain for more than a decade.

title: With Queen Gone, Former Colonies Find a Moment to Rethink Lasting Ties
description: In Commonwealth nations with British colonial histories, Queen Elizabeth’s death is rekindling discussions about a more independent future.

title: Queen Elizabeth’s Coffin Is Moved From Balmoral Castle
description: Queen Elizabeth’s coffin was making a six-hour journey through the Scottish countryside.

title: Ukraine’s Advance in Northeast Renews Pressure on Germany to Help
description: Many weapons Germany promised Kyiv have yet to arrive. Chancellor Olaf Scholz’s government has not fully explained the delays.

title: Britain’s Mourning Rituals
description: Britons are surrounded by visible symbols of Queen Elizabeth II’s death but relatively reserved in their grief.

title: Queen Elizabeth’s coffin is moved from Balmoral Castle, beginning its procession.
description: The queen’s coffin will be moved to Edinburgh, where it will stay until it is flown to London on Tuesday.

title: Ukraine Begins Shutdown of Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant
description: External power has been restored to the plant, allowing engineers to move its reactors into a safer state, Ukraine’s nuclear regulator said.

title: Updates: Queen to Lie in State in Scotland Before Journey to London
description: The queen’s coffin will be taken on Sunday from Balmoral Castle, in the Scottish Highlands, to Edinburgh, where the royal family will gather for ceremonies.

title: Live Updates: Ukrainian Forces Appear to Advance Further After Blitz in North
description: The Ukrainian military was poised to recapture more towns held by Russians after a week of fighting that has reshaped the war.

title: Russia says that a senior Chinese official expressed support for the invasion of Ukraine.
description: The comments are the clearest sign of support from China, which has preferred to stay on the sidelines and maintain ties with both Russia and Europe, without alienating either.

title: Just Bread and Noodles: China’s Covid Lockdown Distress Hits Xinjiang
description: With lack of food, medicine and other crucial supplies, residents of Yining are chafing under a monthlong pandemic shutdown.

title: Ukrainian Offensive Seen as Reshaping the War’s Contours
description: The fall of the strategically important city of Izium, in Ukraine’s east, is the most devastating blow to Russia since its humiliating retreat from Kyiv.

title: Pakistan Is Devastated by Floods, Faces Looming Food Crisis
description: The flooding has crippled Pakistan’s agricultural sector, battering the country as it reels from an economic crisis and double-digit inflation that has sent the price of basics soaring.

title: Chinese Drones: The Latest Irritant Buzzing Taiwan’s Defenses
description: Drones are increasingly testing Taiwan’s capacity to respond to China's growing military pressure. Soldiers shot one down recently and are ramping up defenses.
